{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17658332","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17658332"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:46:24+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:46:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20728"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"20728","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/20728"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.05,0.86,0.05,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"13604"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96911"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"13604","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13604"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20728"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79526"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"11578"},{"type":"tags","id":"11759"},{"type":"tags","id":"12605"},{"type":"tags","id":"12795"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"32710"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32712"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96911","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/96911"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EModular signalling hubs are essential components of cellular signalling networks.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary function of modular signalling hubs in intracellular signalling?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Directly phosphorylate target proteins","Generate second messengers like cyclic adenosine monophosphate","Integrate and coordinate multiple signalling pathways","Degrade signalling proteins after pathway activation","Transcribe genes in response to extracellular signals"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is that modular signalling hubs \u003Cstrong\u003Eintegrate and coordinate multiple signalling pathways\u003C/strong\u003E. These hubs contain specific domains (such as SH2 or SH3) that mediate protein-protein interactions, allowing them to physically connect different signalling molecules and promote the assembly of protein complexes. By influencing which proteins are recruited to signalling complexes, these hubs determine downstream signalling events and coordinate cellular responses.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirectly phosphorylate target proteins\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the role of kinases, not modular signalling hubs. While hubs may contain or recruit kinases, the hubs themselves coordinate rather than perform enzymatic activities.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGenerate second messengers like cyclic adenosine monophosphate\u003C/strong\u003E - Second messengers are produced by enzymes like adenylyl cyclase, not by signalling hubs.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDegrade signalling proteins after pathway activation\u003C/strong\u003E - Protein degradation is typically mediated by the ubiquitin-proteasome system, not by signalling hubs.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETranscribe genes in response to extracellular signals\u003C/strong\u003E - Gene transcription is performed by RNA polymerase and regulated by transcription factors, not signalling hubs.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EModern understanding of cell signalling recognises that signal transduction is a complex network rather than a linear pathway. In this network, modular signalling hubs act as nodes where multiple pathways converge and from which various outputs emerge. These hubs are crucial for integrating diverse signals and coordinating appropriate cellular responses.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Modular signalling hubs organise intracellular signalling pathways by physically linking different enzymes and promoting the assembly of protein complexes.","Signal transduction is a complex network rather than a linear pathway, with modular signalling hubs acting as nodes where multiple pathways converge.","Modular signalling hubs contain specific domains (such as SH2 or SH3) that mediate protein-protein interactions to integrate and coordinate cellular responses."],"references":["Kumar V, Abbas AK, Aster JC. Robbins and Cotran Pathologic Basis of Disease. 10th ed. Philadelphia: Elsevier; 2020. Chapter 1, The Cell as a Unit of Health and Disease;  p. 19"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79526"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20728"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79526","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/79526"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-04-03T13:02:06+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-03T13:16:48+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"13604"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96911"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"11578","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11578"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"The cell as a unit of health and disease","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":0,"createdAt":"2025-02-26T15:05:04+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-02-26T15:05:04+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"da